# Claude Code Rules for Portfolio Project

## Stack
- Astro (no React, no TypeScript)
- SCSS only (no Tailwind)
- pnpm as package manager
- Minimal JavaScript (only when necessary for interactivity)

## Code Style
- Use design tokens from src/styles/tokens/
- Component-scoped SCSS files
- Modern SCSS with @use and @forward (not @import)
- File-based routing in src/pages/

## Developer Context
- User is proficient in HTML/CSS/SCSS
- User is learning JavaScript - explain JS concepts when introducing them
- User prefers clean, readable code over clever abstractions
- User wants to understand what's happening, not just copy-paste

## Project Goals
- Build a portfolio site to showcase design work
- Learn modern web development workflows
- Understand component architecture via Astro
- Practice Git branching and deployment